## Directory Structure Best Practices

### Do's

✅ **DO** organize backend code by feature/domain (feature-based structure)  
✅ **DO** keep related files together within feature modules (models, schemas, routers, services for same feature)  
✅ **DO** use consistent naming conventions across the project  
✅ **DO** separate concerns (presentation, business logic, data access)  
✅ **DO** keep configuration files at appropriate levels  
✅ **DO** document complex directory structures  
✅ **DO** place shared/core code in `app/core/` for cross-cutting concerns  
✅ **DO** create new features following the established feature module structure

### Don'ts

❌ **DON'T** create deeply nested directory structures unnecessarily  
❌ **DON'T** mix concerns (e.g., API routes in model files)  
❌ **DON'T** commit generated files or dependencies  
❌ **DON'T** create circular dependencies between modules  
❌ **DON'T** place environment-specific config in version control  
❌ **DON'T** create duplicate or redundant directory structures

